<!-- ===== org-policy (synced — do not edit by hand) ===== -->

## Branching policy

Before any code edit, ask the user what this work is:

  "A ProofOfBrain board card (W##-NN, e.g. W20-04), a Linear ticket (BE-##), or ad-hoc?"

Then create a branch:

  - ProofOfBrain card      : git checkout -b W##-NN/<short-kebab-slug>   (e.g. W20-04/known-limitations)
  - Linear ticket / ad-hoc : git checkout -b <type>/<slug>              (type ∈ chore, feat, fix, docs, hotfix, infra, refactor)

A Linear ticket rides a <type>/ branch and is attached at PR time, not in the branch name.
Never edit on main, dev, develop, or master. Those branches are blocked org-wide.

For a ProofOfBrain card, read the board card before editing:
  Proof-labs/ProofOfBrain → delivery/boards/YYYY-Www.md → heading "### W##-NN — <title>"

## Pull-request policy

When you open a PR, set the optional "Task link" in the body — ask once if you don't already know it:
  - W##-NN  (ProofOfBrain board card)
  - BE-##   (Linear ticket)
  - No — free-styling for now

Free text is fine. The "Board item / validate" check is advisory and never blocks a merge.
From the terminal, `bash .github/open-pr.sh` asks the same question, then runs `gh pr create`.

